<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
Noonie you said you liked the spell. Does that mean you feel VI was right on target with it in the form it is now? I think most mages love the spell but the cost and needing another class skill to make it work is what makes it not a good functional spell.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
The only thing i would like to see changed is either cut the talismans casting time down to 15 seconds, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>or</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> lower the alchemy cost to 75 pp. Either is an acceptable change.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
What other caster class have a spell that requires this type of reagent? None I believe.<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Necros can rez for 93% if they use an ee which costs roughly 300 pp. <br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
So Noonie you are most likely the only mage out there that is happy with this spell in present form<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Thats only because most mages really have not thought about the applications for this spell. Its like with mod rod, people thought it was going to be useless until they realized what it allowed them to do.<br>
<br>
Giving a mage the ability to change their bind point at will can be quite useful. Elminating the need for a porting class in a dungeon, or allowing a mage to fill that spot as well is very much a huge boon. Maybe not so much in this expansion where evacing is trivialized, however in the next expansion which is rummored to be more dungeon heavy it will.<br>
<br>
Its like necro rez, it gives mages a situational but very useful new ability. <br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Zaniel</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->:<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>100pp is chicken feed at this level of the game. I'm bound somewhere really ugly for the benefit of the guild so I can COH them all in, this spell allows me to be bound there and still move around freely.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
So true. 100pp really is not all that much for the potential this spell offers. It might be a little expensive, but its not outrageous.<br>
This is a situational spell. People just dont understand that. We are not a porting class, but we now have the ability to port for a large, but reasonable fee. Im sorry if i fail to see the downside or how horrible this spell is.<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Sure it'd be cool to be less expensive or perhaps a brewing/research skill made item instead of alchemy but its not so bad as y'all like to pretend. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
