<br>
It's worthless as a backup tool, as the only situation it could be argued to be usefull is for an LD player, and if the 30 second cast time doesn't get them killed then the item is NO RENT so it will most likely be gone by the time they get back from their connection problems.<br>
<br>
As for the raid leaders, I can assure you, if you die away from the raid then they'll get someone to drag your corpse to the raid group and get a rez.  If you can't get dragged, they'll get a necro/sk to summon you, as summoning the corpse is cheaper and they then don't have to get you back in from Plane of Knowledge.  If you can't be summoned other than to zoneline, they'll collect you on their way out. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=59365" target="top">Kathodos</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - Battle Cleric of Tunare - Tholuxe Paells<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=279732" target="top">Kantreach</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - Arch Mage Antagonist - Tholuxe Paells</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=izarek>Izarek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 177<br> <font color=#333333>(2/10/03 1:32:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=163.topic&index=60>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Although expensive and a pain it could be usefull</span><hr size=1> This spell summons a NO RENT version of the quested clockwork talismans with only one charge.<br>
<br>
Its certainly a situational spell.  But I can see a few uses:<br>
- Give to people who have the small clockwork talisman (although rechargable, only holds 5 charges) and save them a charge.<br>
- Carry around stones and make it an expensive TL (although cheaper than gate potions)<br>
- Giving yourself a second bind point.  If you are hunting in a particular place for a while, being able to gate back there is very useful.  But eventually you'll want to head back to civilization.  Hopefully by then you've made back the 100pp the PoK gate is gonna cost you.<br>
- Great for melee soloers who want to gate back after a long day of soloing.  They could carry around gate potions.  But this is still cheaper.  The magician is a master of potential magic.  Capture a TL into an item that can be used hours later.  Not the best.  But the cheapest.<br>
<br>
/shrug. If you don't like this spell don't use it. Don't buy it.  It makes it cheaper for those that want to buy it (at a time when most 61/62 mage spells were 3k, I bought this one for 500pp)<br>
